The uMgungundlovu education district office in Pietermaritzburg was gutted by fire. The fire was reportedly deliberately started by unknown suspects. According to the Kwazulu-Natal Department of education it is not yet clear why the office was set of fire. Provincial Education MEC Kwazi Mshengu said no one was injured in the "arson attack". Mshengu said important administration documents, computers and other administration equipment were lost in the fire. In the video, fire can be seen coming out through the windows of the top floor. Mshengu said the incident will absolutely cause unnecessary delays in curriculum delivery. 